- `useResizeObserver` (`@react-hook/resize-observer`) — check if already in extensions deps; if not, inline a `ResizeObserver` effect
- `forwardRef` + `displayName` required (Pigment v1 pattern)

### FavoriteButton (internal Atom)

```ts
type FavoriteButtonProps = {
  isFavorited: boolean;
  onToggle: (event: React.MouseEvent | React.KeyboardEvent) => void;
  showTooltip?: boolean;
  size?: 'sm' | 'md';
  'aria-label'?: string;
  className?: string;
  style?: React.CSSProperties;
};
```

**Implementation notes:**
- Port visual design from `catalog/features/favorites/FavoriteButton.tsx`
- Remove `useFavorites()` — state is fully external (isFavorited + onToggle as props)
- Remove `SxProps` / MUI — CSS modules
- Keep `HeartIcon` / `HeartFilledIcon` from `@customink/pigment-react`
- Keep `Tooltip` wrapper for `showTooltip` — use local `Tooltip` atom (v0 passthrough)
- `forwardRef` + `displayName`

### Tooltip (internal Atom)

**Status: ✅ Implemented** — `Atoms/Tooltip/Tooltip.tsx`

Pure CSS + React state. No external lib. Hover/focus triggered, CSS opacity transition, arrow via border trick.
- `Tooltip` v0 is not on the public API (only in `v0/index.ts`) — cannot be imported from extensions
- `@floating-ui/react` not needed — simple bottom/top placement is sufficient for FavoriteButton
- No new dependency

### LoadingSkeleton (internal Atom)

```ts
type LoadingSkeletonProps = {
  className?: string;
  style?: React.CSSProperties;
};
```

**Implementation notes:**
- Port `CarouselSkeleton` from `catalog/features/TrendingProducts/components/LoadingSkeleton.jsx`
- Remove MUI `styled` / `keyframes` — use CSS modules with `@keyframes`
- Replace hardcoded colors with `var(--token-*)` CSS custom properties
- 4-card shimmer grid layout

### RecommendationsProductCard (internal Molecule)

```ts
type RecommendationsProductCardProps = {
  name: string;
  linkHref: string;
  imageSrc: string;
  imageSrcSet?: string;
  imageAlt?: string;
  minQty: number;
  ratingScore?: number;
  ratingCount?: number;
  defaultUnitPrices: UnitPrice[];
  defaultQuoteQty: number;
  onClick?: React.MouseEventHandler;
  /** Slot for FavoriteButton overlay (positioned top-right of image) */
  imageOverlay?: React.ReactNode;
  /** Slot for custom price rendering (catalog injects ProductCardPriceDetails) */
  renderPriceDetails?: () => React.ReactNode;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
  style?: React.CSSProperties;
};
```

**Implementation notes:**
- Port visual structure from `catalog/product_details_page/RelatedProducts/RelatedProductCard.jsx`
- Use `Card`, `CardContent`, `Typography`, `Stack`, `Box`, `Link` from `@customink/pigment-react` (v0 backward-compat is fine for fast-track)
- Remove `ProductCardPriceDetails` — render `renderPriceDetails?.()` in its place, or fall back to a basic price display from `defaultUnitPrices[0]` if no render prop given
- Remove `FavoriteButton` import — render `imageOverlay` prop in position: absolute top-right slot
- Remove catalog-specific: `processImageUrl`, `searchParams`, `useMobileBreakpoint` (use local CSS / media query)
- Basic rating display: star score + count (can use `Typography` for now, or port `ProductCardRating`)
- `forwardRef` + `displayName`
- CSS modules, no MUI sx, no hardcoded colors

### ProductCardRating (internal, inside RecommendationsProductCard or standalone)

- Port from `catalog/features/products/components/ProductCard/components/ProductCardRating`
- Or: render rating as plain `Typography` in phase 1, extract to atom later

---

## useTrendingProducts Hook (public)

```ts
type TrendingProductsFetcher = () => Promise<TrendingProduct[]>;

type UseTrendingProductsOptions = {
  fetcher: TrendingProductsFetcher;
  enabled?: boolean;
};

type UseTrendingProductsResult = {
  products: TrendingProduct[];
  isLoading: boolean;
  isError: boolean;
};

function useTrendingProducts(options: UseTrendingProductsOptions): UseTrendingProductsResult;
```

**Implementation notes:**
- Dumb hook: calls `fetcher()`, manages `loading`/`error`/`data` state with `useEffect` + `useState`
- No React Query, no catalog API wiring — those stay in catalog
- No in-memory cache for phase 1 (simple `useEffect`, re-fetches on mount)
- `enabled` flag: skip fetch when `false` (matches catalog `useTrendingProducts` pattern)
- Returns empty `products: []` on error (same behavior as current catalog hook)

**Catalog usage:**
```ts
// catalog: useTrendingProductsWrapper.js wraps this
const { products, isLoading } = useTrendingProducts({
  fetcher: () => fetchPromotionalProducts({ categoryId, limit: 20 }),
  enabled: true,
});
```

---

## TrendingProductsWidget Assembly

**Responsive slidesPerView logic** (preserve from `TrendingCarousel.jsx`):

| Breakpoint | Products count | slidesPerView | spacing |
|---|---|---|---|
| Mobile (`≤ 768px`) | ≥ 3 | 1.6 | 8px |
| Mobile | < 3 | `'auto'` | 8px |
| Desktop | ≥ 5 | 4 | 16px |
| Desktop | < 5 | `'auto'` | 16px |

**Arrow visibility:** `showArrows = slidesPerView !== 'auto' && !isMobile`

**Widget behavior:**
- `isLoading` → render `LoadingSkeleton`
- `products.length === 0` → return `null`
- Viewport visibility: `IntersectionObserver` on wrapper → `onWidgetViewed(products)` fires once
- Card click → `onCardClicked(product, index)`
- Card in viewport → `onCardViewed(product, index)` (per-card IntersectionObserver, optional phase 2)

**`FavoritesProvider` is NOT wrapped here** — catalog is responsible for wrapping:
```tsx
// catalog (after migration)
<FavoritesProvider pageType={PageType.SUBCATEGORY}>
  <TrendingProductsWidget
    products={products}
    isLoading={isLoading}
    renderFavoriteButton={(product) => (
      <FavoriteButton
        styleId={product.styleId}
        isFavorited={isFavorited(product.styleId)}
        onToggle={...}
      />
    )}
    renderPriceDetails={(product) => (
      <ProductCardPriceDetails
        defaultUnitPrices={product.defaultUnitPrices}
        productId={product.styleId}
        quantity={product.defaultQuoteQty}
        {...catalogSpecificProps}
      />
    )}
  />
</FavoritesProvider>
```

---

## Public Exports (`reco/index.ts`)

```ts
export { TrendingProductsWidget } from './TrendingProductsWidget';
export { useTrendingProducts } from './useTrendingProducts';
export type { TrendingProduct, TrendingProductsWidgetProps } from './TrendingProductsWidget/types';
```

Atoms and Molecules are **NOT exported**. No deep imports from catalog.

---

## Storybook Story

Location: `apps/storybook/stories/extensions/reco/TrendingProductsWidget.stories.tsx`

Stories to cover:
1. `Default` — 5+ products, no favorites, no custom price
2. `Loading` — `isLoading=true`, shows skeleton
3. `FewProducts` — 2 products, `slidesPerView='auto'`
4. `WithFavoriteButton` — `renderFavoriteButton` injected (mock state)
5. `Mobile` — responsive viewport story

Use static mock data. No real API calls in Storybook.

---

## Implementation Phases

### Phase 0 — Dependency audit (before coding)
- [ ] Open DS review request for `keen-slider` in `packages/extensions/package.json`
- [ ] Confirm `@react-hook/resize-observer` is already available or inline a `ResizeObserver` effect

### Phase 1 — Types + Internal atoms (parallel)
- [ ] `types.ts`
- [ ] `Atoms/Carousel/` (keen-slider, CSS modules, arrows)
- [ ] `Atoms/FavoriteButton/` (presentational, no context)
- [ ] `Atoms/Tooltip/` (v0 passthrough)
- [ ] `Atoms/LoadingSkeleton/` (CSS modules shimmer)

### Phase 2 — Molecule
- [ ] `Molecules/RecommendationsProductCard/` (with `imageOverlay` + `renderPriceDetails` slots)

### Phase 3 — Hook
- [ ] `useTrendingProducts` (dumb, fetcher injection)
- [ ] Unit tests

### Phase 4 — Widget assembly
- [ ] `TrendingProductsWidget.tsx` (compose atoms + molecule, viewport observer, responsive logic)
- [ ] `TrendingProductsWidget.test.tsx`

### Phase 5 — Exports + Stories
- [ ] `reco/index.ts` barrel
- [ ] Storybook stories

### Phase 6 — Catalog integration (separate PR in catalog)
- [ ] Replace `TrendingCarousel.jsx` usage with import from `@customink/pigment-extensions/reco`
- [ ] Update `useTrendingProductsWrapper` to pass fetcher to `useTrendingProducts`
- [ ] Wrap with `FavoritesProvider` + inject `renderFavoriteButton`
- [ ] Inject `renderPriceDetails`

---

## Tech Debt Tickets to Create (one per component)

| Component | Tier | When to graduate |
|---|---|---|
| `Carousel` | Atom | When DS ships v1 Carousel |
| `FavoriteButton` | Atom | When DS ships v1 FavoriteButton |
| `Tooltip` | Atom (v0 wrapper) | When DS ships v1 Tooltip |
| `RecommendationsProductCard` | Molecule | When DS ships `ProductCard` atom |

---

## DS Enforcement Checklist (per ADR-20)

- [ ] No hardcoded color/spacing values — use `var(--token-*)` CSS custom properties only
- [ ] `@customink/pigment-react` used as peer dep (not bundled)
- [ ] Storybook story exists for `TrendingProductsWidget`
- [ ] `keen-slider` dep reviewed by DS before merge
- [ ] `npm run lint+format:fix` passes
- [ ] `npm run validate` exits 0
- [ ] Storybook starts and renders widget story without errors

